MODIFICATIONS made by the Sourdough Monitor project
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

File: vl53l1x.cpp

  Five calls to the ESPHome i2c helper methods write_register16() and
  read_register16() were updated to drop a 4th argument (a boolean "stop"
  flag). Recent versions of ESPHome changed these method signatures from
  four parameters to three — the I2C stop condition is now handled
  internally. The upstream component was written against the older 4-arg
  API and failed to compile against current ESPHome ("candidate expects 3
  arguments, 4 provided").

  The change is purely an API-compatibility fix. I2C behavior is unchanged.
  Affected call sites (line numbers as of the upstream version bundled):
  919, 927, 939, 943, 947 — each lost a trailing ", true" or ", false".

No other files in this directory were modified.
